SUMMARY:Tempest - St. Patrick's Day Celebration!
DESCRIPTION:Celebrating 37 years of Celtic Rock! \nSince forming in 1988\, Tempest has delivered a globally-renowned hybrid of high-energy Folk Rock\, fusing Irish reels\, Scottish ballads\, Norwegian influences and other world music elements. The last 30-plus years have seen the San Francisco Bay Area-based act release eighteen critically acclaimed albums\, and play more than 2\,500 gigs. \nThe current line-up of the band features all the original members\, performing a variety of selections from the band’s extensive repertoire\, sparking with vitality and energy. \nHailing from Oslo\, Norway\, founder and lead singer/electric mandolinist\, Lief Sorbye\, is recognized as a driving force in the modern folk-rock movement. He started Tempest after years of touring and recording on the folk circuit. \nHe is joined by Bay Area native Rob Wullenjohn on guitar and San Diego’s Ian Butler on bass. Rob and Ian rejoined the band after performing an impromptu reunion concert in Berkeley\, California\, that rekindled the original spirit of Tempest. \nVermont born fiddler Jon Berger first joined the band in 1993. He is now back\, bringing his passion for Celtic and British Isles traditional music. \nAudience favorite\, Cuban-born drummer Adolfo Lazo\, thickens the band’s sound with inventive rhythms\, and rock-steady drumming. After more than three decades Adolfo has never missed a Tempest gig! \nTempest is regularly featured at prestigious festivals such as The Philadelphia Folk Festival\, and has also appeared at Denmark’s Skagen Festival\, Britain’s Cropredy Festival and The Winnipeg Folk Festival in Canada. The band is a mainstay at countless American Celtic festivals\, as well. \nWhile signed to Progressive Rock label Magna Carta records Tempest released a number of critically acclaimed albums over the years. However their latest album “Going Home’ was produced on their own independent label\, and it’s one of their best to date!
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/tempest-st-patricks-day-celebration/
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern – Sebastopol\, 230 Petaluma Ave\, Sebastopol\, CA
CATEGORIES:Holiday,Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Tempest-celtic-rock-s.jpg
GEO:38.4012;-122.823
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=HopMonk Tavern – Sebastopol 230 Petaluma Ave Sebastopol CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=230 Petaluma Ave:geo:-122.823,38.4012
END:VEVENT
